				<span class="tab"></span>PlantFuncSSRs provides the SSRs information accompanied with the primer pair 

information for more than 300 plants species including model as well as well as non-model 

species in a easy to browse and user-friendly format. For the accomplishment of the above task, 

Ruby rails, MYSQL functionalities have been integrated so that the user can easily extract the 

information and the resource can be sustainably used for ecological explorations. We believe that 

the availability of the above resource will aid the rapid development of SSRs-FDM-based 

markers for application in plant breeding programs and development of genetic conservation 

approaches for non-model plant species. We greatly appreciate your feedback on the further 

improvement and continued development of PlantFuncSSRs for ecological explorations.
